This is a graph of the train ids. Each train has a unique id.

Note that the echo = FALSE parameter was added to the code chunk to prevent printing of the R code that generated the plot.

The status chart shows if the train is on time, is running late or suspended. Note that 5 mins late is still considered on time. 999 indicates the train has been suspended.

status_chart <-ggplot(train_data, aes(x = train_data$status)) +
  geom_bar() +
   theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90, hjust=1))

status_chart

Next arrival station for the train.

nextstatn_chart <- ggplot(train_data, aes(x = train_data$next_station)) +
  geom_bar() +
   theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90, hjust=1))

 nextstatn_chart

The train only goes to the North or South. Graph shows these directions for the train.

direction_chart <- ggplot(train_data, aes(x = train_data$direction)) +
  geom_bar()

 direction_chart

Origin shows the stations the train came from.

origin_chart <- ggplot(train_data, aes(x = train_data$origin)) +
  geom_bar() +
   theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle=90, hjust=1))

 origin_chart
